# HITL Ask Questions - Kit-wide confirmations via AskQuestion

Agent Kit uses **Ask questions** tool (`AskQuestion` / ACP `cursor/ask_question`) for **ALL** human-in-the-loop confirmations, choices among options, and clarifications before acting. This creates clickable options in the IDE UI instead of plain-text "type yes to continue" prompts.

## Contract for Agent Kit

1. **Any step that needs confirmation, choice among options, or clarification before acting** must call **Ask questions**, not ask the user to type. **No exceptions** for onboarding or install.

2. **Prefer one question at a time** (or a small coherent set in one tool call if the product allows multi-question).

3. **Options must be concrete labels** (e.g. `Write plan file`, `Create first plan`, `Skip for now`, `Install via CLI`, `Install via chat`, `Start first unit`, `Switch to /run-plan`).

4. **Fallback when tool unavailable:** some models/modes do not expose the tool (dogfood 2026-07-20: Auto mode routed picks and Grok 4.5 absent; Opus, Sonnet 4.6, Composer 2.5 Fast, GPT, Gemini present — see `.cursor/memory/decisions/2026-07-20_ask-questions-model-availability.md`). When it is not in the session toolset, say so once, then present the same options in chat as a **numbered list**. Tell the user they can **reply with the number** (or the label), and that they can always **type their own answer** (the equivalent of the built-in "Other" choice) if none fit. Do not invent a fake tool call. Tip: switching to a model that supports Ask questions restores the clickable UI.

5. **This does not weaken HITL:** skipped/cancelled answers mean **stop** (same as no yes).

## Gates requiring Ask questions

| Surface | Gate |
|---------|------|
| `install.md` (Port B / drag-install) | Registry URL/ref if needed; create first plan yes/no; migrate nested `agent-kit/` confirm; optional git-hooks install |
| `/onboard` | First-session welcome; workspace skin pick (Keep mode defaults / Autopilot / Night Shift / Ghost Runner / Skip); Create first plan / Skip for now / Learn more; already-onboarded: Start a plan / Continue plan / Change workspace skin / Show commands overview / Done |
| `context-guardian` onboarding | Defer to `/onboard` when first install / no `onboarded` marker; auto vs manual handoff preference (first time) |
| `/start-project` | Gate A (write plan?); Gate B (start first unit / run-plan / edit); vague goal clarify |
| `/continue-plan` | Confirm next `[to-do-id]`; if multiple plans, pick which to resume |
| `/git-prod` | Explicit confirm before merge/push to `main` |
| `/run-plan` | Risk pause (PII, secrets, ambiguous scope); not every tick |
| `/plan-review-triage` | Triage choice (write residuals plan / fix nits only / ack and stop) |
| `/handoff` / guardian | Prefer Ask questions when offering auto vs manual handoff |
| Other commands / docs | Any "stop and ask" / "Want to… (yes/no)" prose in L0 + getting-started / bootstrap |

## CLI exception

`agent-kit init` / wizard in `packages/cli/src/utils/prompts.ts` already uses `@clack/prompts` (terminal select/confirm). Keep that. Do not call IDE `AskQuestion` from the CLI. This rule only ensures chat/`install.md` onboarding matches the same UX quality.

